          {
            "title": "Time-effect profile of Levemir",
            "code": {
              "text": "Time-effect of insulin detemir"
            },
            "text": {
              "status": "additional",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><p>Levemir (insulin detemir) is a long-acting basal insulin with a relatively flat time-action profile.</p><ul><li><b>Onset of action:</b> approximately 3–4 hours after subcutaneous injection.</li><li><b>Peak effect:</b> no pronounced peak; glucose-lowering effect is relatively flat over the dosing interval.</li><li><b>Duration of action:</b> up to about 24 hours depending on dose, injection site and individual response.</li></ul></div>"
            },
